article.headline: Gardner-Webb, 72, North Florida 52
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Thomas Sanders scored 19 points off the bench to help lead Gardner-Webb to a 72-52 win against North Florida Thursday. Gardner-Webb (3-10, 1-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) hit 21 of 38 free throws and rallied in the second half to break its four-game losing streak. The Bulldogs outscored North Florida (2-12, 0-4) 45-23 in the final 20 minutes of the game. Takayo Siddle scored 14 points for Gardner-Webb and teammate Matt French ended the night with 13 points. North Florida's Germaine Sparkes scored a career-high 18 points and James Grimball added 15 points and 10 rebounds.
